a society where their national identity is quite regularly under threat. At the same time however, that same closure is perceived to pose a threat to the survival of Estonian culture and independence. This book provides an intimate insight in the lives of Estonians from the countryside, former deportees, young intellectuals and memory activists, who all in their own ways act as guardians of a national history: a history which they wish to keep alive, apolitical and as close to their family stories as possible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aCollective memoryzEstonia. 0aNational characteristics, Estonian. 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Baltic States.2bisacsh  aCollective memory, post-Soviet, nationalism, memory practices, ethnography.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048541430zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048541430423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048541430.jpg  a978-3-11-068955-6  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  a978-3-11-069630-1  PP ROW Eb